# User Rules

## Platform Admin
- **Scope**: Global system access.  
- **Permissions**: Full (create, edit, delete) or view-only.  
- **Capabilities**:  
  - Can assign Platform Admins to accounts.  
  - Cannot see accounts they are not assigned to.  

## Account-level User
### Enterprise User
- **Scope**: Access limited to their Enterprise + its Organizations.  
- **Permissions**: Full or view-only.  
- **Full Capabilities**:  
  - Can add Enterprise Admins within their Enterprise. 
  - Can manage Enterprise settings.  
  - Cannot see Organizations outside their Enterprise or that they're not assigned to.   
- **View-on Capabilities**:  
  - Can view and contribute.  
  - Cannot manage users or accounts.
  
### Organization User 
- **Scope**: Access limited to their Organization.  
- **Permissions**: Full or view-only.  
- **Full Capabilities**:  
  - Can add Organization Users (Admin, User, Patroller).  
  - Can manage Organization settings.  
- **View-Only Capabilities**:  
  - Can log in and view Organization data.  
  - Cannot modify data or manage users.  

##Patroller
- **Scope**: Access limited to their Organization.  
- **Capabilities**:  
  - Can log in and submit reports.  
  - Cannot manage users or settings.  

